Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:54.07,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:111940,114070}Coach, please listen.{NOTE:コーチ。聞いてください。}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.07,0:02:00.03,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:114070,120030}I've thought of a way to receive Borchinskaya's killer spike.{NOTE:私ソ連のボルチンスカヤのあの殺人スパイクをレシーブする方法を考えてみたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.03,0:02:00.91,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:120030,120910}Hm?{NOTE:んん？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:03.20,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:122200,123206}Let's hear it.{NOTE:それで？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.20,0:02:05.66,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:123206,125660}It's still rough around the edges, sir.{NOTE:はい。未だほんのヒントの段階なんですけれども…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.66,0:02:08.00,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:125660,128003}But I figured it out after our game with South Korea was over…{NOTE:この前韓国との試合が終わった時…}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.00,0:02:11.63,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:128003,131630}…and a boy named Johnny stole our mascot ball.{NOTE:…ジョニーって言う少年が私達のマスコットボールを持って行ったんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:13.96,Default,Yoshimura,0,0,0,,{TIME:132670,133960}What a beautiful nighttime view.{NOTE:綺麗な夜景。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.96,0:02:15.55,Default,Yoshimura,0,0,0,,{TIME:133960,135550}You just don't get these in Tōkyō.{NOTE:東京と思うとは違って。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:18.22,Default,Noda,0,0,0,,{TIME:135550,138220}We should go down there some time and see it all.{NOTE:たまに私達もXXX来た。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:21.97,Default,Kakinouchi,0,0,0,,{TIME:138220,141970}When the games are over, we'll ask Coach to take us.{NOTE:全て試合が終わったらコーチが連れてってくれるのよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.97,0:02:26.52,Alternative,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:141970,146520}Dear Papa. Today we defeated Romania in the semifinals.{NOTE:パパ。私達は今日準決勝でルーマニアを破りました。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.52,0:02:28.69,Alternative,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:146520,148690}The day after tomorrow we'll play our final game.{NOTE:いよいよ明後日は決勝戦。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.69,0:02:30.65,Alternative,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:148690,150650}We'll probably play against the USSR.{NOTE:多分XXXソ連と。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.65,0:02:32.65,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:150650,152650}Hey, why don't we play cards?{NOTE:め、みんなでトランプしない？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.65,0:02:33.82,Default,Yoshimura,0,0,0,,{TIME:152650,153820}Good idea!{NOTE:やりましょう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.82,0:02:35.82,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:153820,155820}Hayakawa-san, come play with us, too.{NOTE:早川さんもいらっしゃいよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:36.36,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:155820,156360}Okay.{NOTE:え。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.36,0:02:37.82,Default,Arai,0,0,0,,{TIME:156360,157820}Ah, what about Captain?{NOTE:あれ？キャプテンは？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.82,0:02:42.45,Default,Miyatsu,0,0,0,,{TIME:157820,162450}I just saw her in the hallway going to Coach's room.{NOTE:そう言えばさっき廊下でコーチの部屋の方へ行くの見たっすよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.45,0:02:43.99,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:162450,163990}I see.{NOTE:あらそう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.99,0:02:46.66,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:163990,166660}She's probably discussing strategies with him.{NOTE:きっと作戦のことで何か話があるのよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.66,0:02:48.54,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:166660,168540}Let's start already. Come on.{NOTE:さ、やりましょうよ。ね、速く。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.54,0:02:49.58,Default,(mixed),0,0,0,,{TIME:168540,169580}– Yeah.\N– Okay.{NOTE:—え。\\N—え。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.63,0:02:53.17,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:171630,173170}Keep going.{NOTE:さきを続けたまえ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.17,0:02:54.04,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:173170,174040}Sir.{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.04,0:02:59.34,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:174040,179340}I saw Johnny practicing soccer very hard\Nwith the ball he'd stolen.{NOTE:私はそこでジョニーが奪っていたボールで一所懸命サッカーの練習をしているのを見たんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:04.43,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:183300,184430}His speed…{NOTE:あのスピード。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.43,0:03:06.06,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:184430,186060}But especially his forcefulness…{NOTE:それにあの力。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:08.52,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:186060,188520}It was sharp like Borchinskaya's killer spike.{NOTE:殺人スパイクのように鋭い。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.52,0:03:11.52,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:188520,191520}But when Virginia called him out…{NOTE:でも、バージニアが声をかけた時…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.56,0:03:15.48,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:193560,195480}The ball hit him in head…{NOTE:ヘッディングやり損なった時…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.53,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:195480,199530}And it lost its force and fell behind him like a deflated balloon.{NOTE:後ろへ飛んだボールはまるで風船のように力がなくなっていた。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.53,0:03:21.45,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:199530,201450}So, then I thought to myself…{NOTE:そこで私は思いついたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:26.45,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:201450,206450}Would it be possible to cut the power\Nof the strike in half by relaying it once?{NOTE:強い力で飛んでくるボールを一度中継すれば力が半減するんじゃないかって。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.45,0:03:27.12,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:206450,207120}In other words—{NOTE:つまり…}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.12,0:03:31.04,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:207120,211040}You can receive Borchinskaya's killer spike\Nif you divide the reception in two.{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤの殺人スパイクも二度に分ければレシーブできる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.04,0:03:33.50,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:211040,213500}Precisely. A two-stage reception.{NOTE:そうです。二段レシーブです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.50,0:03:37.46,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:213500,217460}To accomplish it, rather than bumping it\Nto the front, you'd send it back.{NOTE:そのためには前へ返すではなく後ろへ返す。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.46,0:03:39.55,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:217460,219550}E-Exactly!{NOTE:そ、そうなんです！}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:43.43,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:219550,223430}Perhaps Coach noticed me during our training?{NOTE:もしかしたらコーチは特訓にそのことを気がついていたんだわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.47,0:03:45.68,Alternative,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:224470,225680}Hm.{NOTE:んん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:46.97,Alternative,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:225680,226970}You've got us a good strategy.{NOTE:よくヒントをつかんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:49.22,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:228310,229220}Ayuhara.{NOTE:鮎原。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.22,0:03:51.52,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:229220,231520}You did well, coming up with this.{NOTE:よくそこまで生長してくれたな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:53.23,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:231520,233230}Coach, what do you think?{NOTE:コーチ。どうでしょうか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.35,0:03:55.90,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:234350,235900}Don't rush it.{NOTE:そう慌てるな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:58.11,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:235900,238110}As you know, Borchinskaya's spike is…{NOTE:何しろ、ボルチンスカヤのスパイクは…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.37,0:04:19.17,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:254370,259170}Even Manumba, who was such a prominent and fit player…{NOTE:ずば抜けてしなやかな体と強靭なXXを持ったあのマヌンバでさえ…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.17,0:04:23.09,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:259170,263090}…collapsed on the floor from receiving it.\NIt really is a killer spike.{NOTE:コートに崩れねばならなかったことの文字通り殺人的スパイク。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:26.51,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:263090,266510}Also, in practice, it's very hard\Nto play a ball backwards.{NOTE:後ろへレシーブすると言っても、なかなかできるもんではない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:30.22,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:266510,270220}If you make one mistake, you'll only cause great chaos on your side of the court.{NOTE:生半可なことをやれば返って姿勢が崩れてコートに叩きつけられやすい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:39.69,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:276400,279690}But even if you hypothetically succeed with the two-stage reception…{NOTE:それに例え二段レシーブに成功したとしても…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.69,0:04:42.28,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:279690,282280}…the problem is how you launch an attack afterwards.{NOTE:…その後の攻撃をどうするかが問題だ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.28,0:04:46.66,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:282280,286661}Just succeeding at receiving it\Nwon't earn us any points.{NOTE:ただレシーブして返してもそれがポイントに結びつかなかったら何もならんからな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.20,0:04:50.41,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:288200,290410}Then there's the most important problem:{NOTE:それより一番問題なのは…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.41,0:04:53.29,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:290410,293290}Coming up with new exercises at this point.{NOTE:この期に及んで、新しい練習をすることを。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.29,0:04:54.33,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:293290,294330}Huh?{NOTE:え？}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.33,0:04:56.92,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:294330,296920}If you can master it, fine. But if you can't…{NOTE:マスターできればいいがもしできなかったら…}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:05:00.80,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:297580,300800}…you'll just unnecessarily confuse the rest of the team.{NOTE:ただいたずらにメンバーの気持ちを動揺させる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:06.01,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:300800,306010}Furthermore, you'll just make them fear killer spikes even more.{NOTE:そして殺人スパイクに対する恐怖心を必要以上に大きくするだけだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.01,0:05:07.59,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:306010,307590}He's right.{NOTE:その通りだわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:12.77,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:307590,312770}And yet I practiced backwards receptions in front of everyone.{NOTE:なのに私ったら不要にもみんなの前で後ろへのレシーブを練習したりして。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.77,0:05:15.23,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:312770,315230}I'm glad I didn't announce anything yet.{NOTE:でも未だ公表しなくてよかった。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.23,0:05:21.23,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:315230,321230}So before we start training the two-stage reception, we need to be sure that it even works.{NOTE:したがって練習をやる以上二段レシーブを完全にマスター出きるという確信を得てからでなければならん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:27.49,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:322570,327490}That way we can take a look\Nat your suggestion from all angles.{NOTE:そのためにはお前のつかんだヒントもとにもう一度始めから研究し直してみよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.49,0:05:28.49,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:327490,328490}Yes sir.{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.49,0:05:31.91,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:328490,331910}Tomorrow the Soviets play against Czechoslovakia, which is to our favor.{NOTE:丁度上手い具合に明日はソ連対チェコの試合だ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.91,0:05:35.66,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:331910,335660}It's a good opportunity for us\Nto study on the real thing.{NOTE:実物に際して研究させてもらういいチャンスだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.66,0:05:39.29,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:335660,339290}Speaking of Czechoslovakia,\NI remembered their match against Mexico.{NOTE:チェコと言えば、この前に対メキシコ戦の時。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.29,0:05:42.50,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:339290,342500}I can't forget the wonderful revolving receive that Češka did.{NOTE:チェシカの見せた素晴らしい回転レシーブの忘れられません。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:58.69,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:352430,358690}Češka is a cousin of Čáslavská. It seems she learned a lot about gymnastics from her.{NOTE:チェシカはチャスラフスカの従姉妹だがそのチャスラフスカについて体操を徹底的に習ったらしい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:06:01.82,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:358690,361820}Čáslavská, who has been called the queen of gymnastics, is Češka's cousin?{NOTE:体操の女王と言われたチャスラフスカの従姉妹。}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.27,0:06:06.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,{TIME:358270,366030}{\fs38\fad(800,1000)}Věra Čáslavská – a Czechoslovakian artistic gymnast and Czech sports official
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:10.82,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:367280,370820}Borchinskaya's killer spike vs. Češka's revolving receive.{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤの殺人スパイク対チェシカの回転レシーブ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.62,0:06:14.74,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:372620,374740}Ayuhara. Watch them closely.{NOTE:鮎原。よくみておくんだぞ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.74,0:06:15.45,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:374740,375450}Yes sir.{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.69,0:06:44.61,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:402690,404610}Czechoslovakia is doing better than expected.{NOTE:チェコは予想以上にやるわね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:49.65,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:404610,409650}Every time the Soviets serve, Češka instructs the receiver where the ball will land.{NOTE:ソ連がサーブするたびにチェシカがボールの行き先を見定めてレシーバーに指示をする。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.65,0:06:51.07,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:409650,411070}She really has a handle on her team.{NOTE:あのリードが聞いているんだわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.07,0:06:53.66,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:411070,413660}Yes, but the Soviets haven't shown their true power yet.{NOTE:しかしソ連は未だ実力を出しきってはいない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.66,0:06:54.28,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:413660,414280}Huh?{NOTE:え？}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.28,0:06:57.50,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:414280,417500}The proofs right in Borchinskaya's still being on the bench.{NOTE:その証拠にボルチンスカヤは未だベンチにいる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:05.46,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:421880,425460}But I know what's going on in their coach's head.{NOTE:しかし、ソ連コーチのはらん中は読めている。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:09.22,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:425460,429220}He doesn't want to use Borchinskaya in today's game.{NOTE:出きることならこの試合にボルチンスカヤを使いたくはないんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.18,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:429220,431180}He's saving her for tomorrow's finals.{NOTE:明日の決勝戦に備えてな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:16.14,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:432550,436140}But he'll need to have her come out sooner or later.{NOTE:しかし、今に出ざるを得なくなるぞ、今に。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.90,0:07:29.19,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:446900,449190}Wow, she tied the score!{NOTE:あ、タイに打ち込んだわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:33.57,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:449190,453570}One method to break the Soviets' iron block is to aim at the line.{NOTE:ソ連の鉄壁のブロックを破るにはラインぎりぎりを狙うのも一つの方法ね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:36.16,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:453570,456160}It's not a real method. It's a sink-or-swim gamble.{NOTE:方法と言うよりかそれはいちかばちかのかけだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.37,0:07:38.87,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:457374,458870}The risk was too high.{NOTE:危険は多すぎる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.87,0:07:42.79,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:458870,462790}Češka took that bet and won, but it's not going to last long.{NOTE:チェシカの相手XXに出て今勝ったがそれが恐らく限界だろう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.29,0:07:46.29,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:464290,466290}That's just how bets are.{NOTE:掛けとはそういうものだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:49.63,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:468170,469630}Ah, Borchinskaya!{NOTE:わ、ボルチンスカヤ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.39,0:07:57.14,Default,Czech,0,0,0,,{TIME:476390,477140}Ah.{NOTE:あ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.02,0:08:03.85,Default,Russia,0,0,0,,{TIME:483020,483850}Borcha!{NOTE:ボルチャ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.60,0:08:05.44,Default,Borchinskaya,0,0,0,,{TIME:484600,485440}{NOTE:XXX！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:11.65,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:490900,491658}It's over!{NOTE:やった！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:18.83,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:497660,498832}Revolving receive!{NOTE:回転レシーブ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:27.79,Default,Czech,0,0,0,,{TIME:506580,507790}Ah.{NOTE:あ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:30.88,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:509630,510880}Saw that, Ayuhara?{NOTE:鮎原。見たか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.88,0:08:31.55,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:510880,511550}Yes sir.{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:36.18,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:513050,516180}Češka's revolving receive\Nis superior in every way to mine.{NOTE:私より素晴らしいチェシカの空中回転レシーブ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:39.76,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:516180,519760}And yet, she let it slam the court.{NOTE:それさえも寄せ付けずコートに叩きつけるなんて。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.76,0:08:43.94,Alternative,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:519760,523940}Now I understand what Coach meant in the training camp in Miyazaki.{NOTE:宮崎の合宿でコーチに言われた事は今更のように分かったわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.66,0:08:59.41,Default,Kakinouchi,0,0,0,,{TIME:535660,539410}The last set was pretty close,\Nbut this set is completely different.{NOTE:第一セットはXXXだけど、第二セットはXXX。}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:02.62,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:539410,542620}After Češka failed to receive Borchinskaya's spike…{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤのスパイクをチェシカはレシーブしそこなってから…}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.62,0:09:06.12,Default,Sanjou,0,0,0,,{TIME:542620,546120}…Czechoslovakia started to collapse\Nlike a house of cards.{NOTE:…チェコはまるで流れのように崩れていくわね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:10.88,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:546120,550880}Who knows if we're going to be just as powerless tomorrow as Czechoslovakia is today?{NOTE:このチェコの惨めな姿が明日の私達の姿じゃないと誰が言えよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.88,0:09:13.55,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:550880,553550}We've got to think of a way to receive that killer spike.{NOTE:何としても殺人スパイクをレシーブしなければ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.15,0:09:34.99,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:574150,574990}Ayuhara.{NOTE:鮎原。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.99,0:09:36.32,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:574990,576320}Sir!?{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:39.82,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:576320,579820}When the second set is over, bring everyone back to the hotel.{NOTE:第二セットも終わったら全員引き連れてホテルへ戻る。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:41.24,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:579820,581240}Huh?{NOTE:え？}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.24,0:09:45.87,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:581240,585870}In the meantime, I'll try to secure us a place where we can secretly practice the two-stage reception.{NOTE:俺はその間に二段レシーブの練習が秘密のうちにできることを探してみる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:47.50,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:585870,587500}Coach…?{NOTE:コーチ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:50.71,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:587500,590710}I analyzed it all night long.{NOTE:俺は昨夜一晩中をかかって研究しみた。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.21,0:09:57.59,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:592210,597590}But seeing Borchinskaya's spike today has finally convinced me.{NOTE:その結果と今のボルチンスカヤのスパイクを見てやっと自身を得たの。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.59,0:10:01.51,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:597590,601510}To counter Borchinskaya's killer spike,\Nwe're going to need that two-stage reception.{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤの殺人スパイクに二段レシーブを使うこと。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.51,0:10:02.68,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:601510,602680}Coach…{NOTE:コーチ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.68,0:10:03.85,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:602680,603850}Listen, Ayuhara.{NOTE:いいか、鮎原。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:08.94,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:603850,608940}Borchinskaya's killer spike is like South Korean team's Sai's bullet spike.{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤの殺人スパイクは韓国のサイの弾丸スパイクに変化をつけたようなもの。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.94,0:10:12.36,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:608940,612360}Its power and speed are almost the same.{NOTE:その力とスピードはほとんど同じと見ていい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:13.86,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:612360,613860}Oh, Sai-san's spike?{NOTE:あのサイさんの？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.86,0:10:14.90,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:613860,614900}Ops.{NOTE:あ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.90,0:10:18.20,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:614900,618200}Borchinskaya and Sai are roughly the same height.{NOTE:ボルチンスカヤとサイは丁度背の高さも同じくらい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.20,0:10:24.29,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:618200,624290}It would be very convenient if we could practice with someone with a spike such as hers.{NOTE:彼女のようなスパイクの持ち主が家のチームにもいてくれれば練習には好都合なんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.29,0:10:26.25,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:624290,626250}Well, talking won't get things done.{NOTE:ま、そんなデータがXXX。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:28.96,Default,Inokuma,0,0,0,,{TIME:626250,628960}Don't forget what I've just said, Ayuhara.{NOTE:いいか、鮎原。今言った事を忘れんなよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:29.96,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:628960,629960}Yes sir.{NOTE:はい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:39.09,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:636380,639090}Huh? We'll practice a two-stage reception?{NOTE:え？二段レシーブの練習ですって？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.09,0:10:39.97,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:639090,639970}Yep.{NOTE:うん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.97,0:10:44.64,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:639970,644640}Coach went to find us a court where we could practice in secret.{NOTE:コーチは今ね、それを秘密で練習できるコートを探しに行ってるのよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:49.94,Default,Arai,0,0,0,,{TIME:644640,649940}With the two-stage reception\Nwe'll have nothing to be afraid of, right?{NOTE:二段レシーブができれば、あのボルチンスカヤのスパイクも恐れるに足りずってわけがない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:54.94,Default,Yoshimura,0,0,0,,{TIME:649940,654940}But can we really learn\Nthe two-stage reception in just one day?{NOTE:でも、たった一日だけの練習で本当にその二段レシーブがマスターできるのかしら？}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:56.73,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:654940,656730}Oh, that must be Coach.{NOTE:あ、コーチよ、きっと。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.73,0:10:58.74,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:656730,658740}Hai? Oh, I mean…{NOTE:はい！あ、行けない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.74,0:11:00.20,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:658740,660200}Yes?{NOTE:Yes?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:02.24,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:660200,662240}It's not our coach…?{NOTE:何だ、コーチじゃなかったわ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.24,0:11:03.12,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:662240,663120}What?{NOTE:は？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:03.91,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:663120,663910}Sai?{NOTE:サイ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:09.50,Default,Sai,0,0,0,,{TIME:666870,669500}I must have surprised you,\Npaying you a sudden visit like this.{NOTE:私が突然訪ねてきてびっくりしてますね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.50,0:11:10.92,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:669500,670920}Huh? Oh, no.{NOTE:え？あ、いいえ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.92,0:11:12.58,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:670920,672580}Heh. Well, I guess you're right.{NOTE:ふふ。え、本当わ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:18.51,Default,Sai,0,0,0,,{TIME:672580,678510}Actually, I overheard you and your coach talking about me at the Central Gymnasium.{NOTE:実は私さっきセントラル体育館であなたとコーチが私のことを喋ってるの聞いていたんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:19.55,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:678510,679550}Huh?{NOTE:え？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:22.05,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:679550,682050}Then you heard about\Nthe two-stage reception as well?{NOTE:じゃ、れいの二段レシーブの話も？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.05,0:11:23.34,Default,Sai,0,0,0,,{TIME:682050,683340}Yes. That too.{NOTE:はい。そのことも。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.60,0:11:28.10,Default,Hayakawa,0,0,0,,{TIME:684600,688100}So by "Sai" she meant\NSouth Korean's captain, Sai-san?{NOTE:サイって韓国チームのキャプテンのサイさんのことだったの。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:31.39,Default,Yoshimura,0,0,0,,{TIME:688100,691390}We've struggled a lot with her bullet spike.{NOTE:弾丸スパイク。私達散々苦しめられたわね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.39,0:11:34.11,Default,Arai,0,0,0,,{TIME:691390,694110}What does Sai-san need with our captain?{NOTE:そのサイさんはキャプテンに何のようXだろう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.40,0:11:36.36,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:695400,696360}Huh?{NOTE:え？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:40.61,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:696360,700610}You'll really come play with us at our practice?{NOTE:じゃ、あの、サイさんは私達の練習に協力してくださるんですか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:43.66,Default,Sai,0,0,0,,{TIME:700610,703660}The pleasure is all mine.\NI hope I can be of use to you.{NOTE:私でお役に立つのだったら、喜んで。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.66,0:11:45.91,Default,Ayuhara,0,0,0,,{TIME:703660,705910}Thank you, Sai-san!{NOTE:わ、有難うサイさん。}
